        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 11 at 4:08PM EDT by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg SC</headline>
        <description>At 407 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 7
miles southeast of Gastonia, or 5 miles south of Cramerton, moving
southeast at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Steele Creek, Tega Cay, Carowinds, Lake Wylie, Fort Mill, Southwest
Charlotte, Cramerton, Gastonia, and Belmont.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
